<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-06-10T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-06-10T12:00:00-05:00" n="795" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d795">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/22164b:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi></persName>)<note n="64" xml:id="d795fn64">Repeated as No. 2631 to the Ambassador in the
                                    United Kingdom and as No. 287 to the Ambassador in the Soviet
                                    Union; message was sent with the approval of President
                                    Roosevelt.</note></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-06-10T13:00:00-04:00">June 10, 1942—1
                                    p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>506. Please inform the Foreign Office confidentially that the
                                Commonwealth of the Philippines has indicated a desire to adhere to
                                Declaration by United Nations; that we find no objection; that in
                                the absence of any objection from the Chinese, British, or Soviet
                                Governments, such adherence will be formally accepted at a White
                                House ceremony on June 14.<note n="65" xml:id="d795fn65">No
                                    objection was made by the three Governments.</note></p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>